# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js portfolio project.

## Implementation Details

### 1. Documentation Review
Fetched the latest official Vercel Speed Insights documentation from:
https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart

Confirmed the project uses Next.js 16.2.5 with App Router, which supports the latest Speed Insights integration pattern.

### 2. Package Installation
Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` version 2.0.0 using npm:
- Command: `npm install @vercel/speed-insights`
- Package added to dependencies in package.json
- package-lock.json updated with new dependencies

### 3. Code Changes
Modified `src/app/layout.tsx`:
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component alongside the existing `<Analytics />` component
- Placed within the `<body>` tag after the `<ThemeProvider>` closing tag
- Follows the same pattern as the existing Vercel Analytics integration

### 4. Verification
✅ Build successful: `npm run build` completed without errors
✅ TypeScript compilation: No type errors
✅ Lint check: No new linting errors introduced by our changes
✅ Static generation: All pages generated successfully

## Files Modified
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new package dependencies
- `src/app/layout.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights component and import

## Next Steps
To view Speed Insights data:
1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard for this project
2. Deploy the changes to Vercel
3. After user visits, access Speed Insights in the dashboard to view performance metrics

## Notes
- The implementation follows the official Next.js App Router pattern
- Speed Insights component is placed alongside the existing Analytics component
- No breaking changes or configuration modifications required
- The component will automatically track Core Web Vitals and performance metrics
